column8: Share one interesting fact about microplastics
When you look out at a window and see bits of dust floating past, those are often microplastics.
I learned that microbeads, which are found in many beauty products and toothpastes, are a major issue as they easily pass through water filtration systems. (National Ocean Service)
46% of the great pacific garbage patch is discarded fishing nets, which eventually break down into microplastics (https://www.nature.com/articles/s41598-018-22939-w)
Not all types of plastic are harmful to our health or the environment. (Source: http://sustonmagazine.com/2018/01/18/facts-you-should-know-about-microplastics/)
